[vc_row full_width="stretch_row_content_no_spaces" overlay_dotted=""][vc_column][havnor_about_me tog_align="" about_me_title="Hello! I am Vincent Munoz" social_icons="%5B%7B%22social_icon%22%3A%22fa%20fa-facebook%22%2C%22social_link%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%22%7D%2C%7B%22social_icon%22%3A%22fa%20fa-twitter%22%2C%22social_link%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twitter.com%22%7D%2C%7B%22social_icon%22%3A%22fa%20fa-google-plus%22%2C%22social_link%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.plus.google.com%22%7D%2C%7B%22social_icon%22%3A%22fa%20fa-instagram%22%2C%22social_link%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Finstagram.com%22%7D%2C%7B%22social_icon%22%3A%22fa%20fa-linkedin%22%2C%22social_link%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%22%7D%5D" about_me_content="Let me introduce myself, I'm Vincent Munoz. Amanda actually asked me to be his best man about 6 months ago when we were in the pub. But I never received a formal invitation to the wedding, so I just hope I haven’t eaten a meal meant for someone else. In fact, I’m sure it was such a simple oversight - or more likely, Paul trying to save the cost of a stamp." btn_text="Contact Me" btn_link="#0"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row overlay_dotted="" css=".vc_custom_1544085603651{padding-top: 9% !important;padding-bottom: 8% !important;}"][vc_column][havnor_section_title title_align="center" title_text="Groom's Basic Quality" btm_space="4%"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner offset="vc_col-lg-6 vc_col-md-6"][hanor_counting_section counting_logos="%5B%7B%22counting_value%22%3A%2201.%22%2C%22counting_title%22%3A%22Commitment%22%2C%22counting_content%22%3A%22We%20are%20deeply%20committed%20to%20the%20long-term%20growth%20and%20success%20of%20our%20clients%20and%20our%20people.%22%7D%2C%7B%22counting_value%22%3A%2202.%22%2C%22counting_title%22%3A%22Teaming%22%2C%22counting_content%22%3A%22We%20believe%20drawing%20leads%20to%20excellent%20results.%20We%20share%20knowledge%2C%20tools%2C%20and%20resources.%22%7D%5D"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner offset="vc_col-lg-6 vc_col-md-6"][hanor_counting_section counting_logos="%5B%7B%22counting_value%22%3A%2203.%22%2C%22counting_title%22%3A%22Planning%22%2C%22counting_content%22%3A%22We%20aim%20to%20deliver%20the%20necessary%20levels%20of%20service%20over%20high%20production%2C%20constant.%22%7D%2C%7B%22counting_value%22%3A%2204.%22%2C%22counting_title%22%3A%22Marriage%22%2C%22counting_content%22%3A%22We%20are%20excited%20about%20what%20we%20do%20and%20who%20we%20are.%20We%20are%20committed%20to%20the%20success%20of%20our%20customers%20and%20our%20people.%20%22%7D%5D"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" overlay_dotted="" css=".vc_custom_1544087092310{padding-top: 6% !important;background-color: #f9f9f9 !important;}"][vc_column][havnor_section_title title_align="center" title_text="Ask About Wedding Plan" content_text="Services focus on our clients' most critical issues and opportunities." btm_space="5%" title_size="36px" title_btm="0px"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" overlay_dotted="" css=".vc_custom_1544087059214{padding-bottom: 9% !important;background-color: #f9f9f9 !important;}"][vc_column offset="vc_col-lg-6 vc_col-md-6"][vc_accordion accordion_style="style-one"][vc_accordion_tab title="Who's responsible for lifting the bride's veil?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Modern veil styles (like boho-chic flower crowns) have encouraged a rewriting of this tradition, but for a traditional veil style that's draped over the bride's face, there are two options. One is to have the father of the bride lift the veil when he gives her away, in a way, revealing her to her partner. The other is for the bride to keep her veil over her face during the ceremony, then have their partner lift it just before the first kiss.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="What side are we supposed to stand on ceremony?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Traditionally, for a Christian ceremony, if you're in a church facing the altar, the bride stands on the left side and the groom on the right. Guests of the bride and groom follow suit, sitting on the side of whomever they know best or are related to. (Hint: Tell mutual friends to sit on the side with fewer people.) For Jewish ceremonies, it's the opposite (aka bride on the right, groom on the left). Many couples also opt for free seating, telling their guests to place themselves wherever they please. If neither of you feel affinity for any religion or tradition in particular, stand however works best for your ceremony.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="What exactly does the couple cutting the cake?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]The cake cutting typically takes place after dinner, but you can also cut a quick slice right after your reception entrance or the toasts wrap up. Draw attention to the event by asking your bandleader or DJ to make an announcement (or one of you can do this). If you have older guests who might be leaving early, cut your cake near the beginning of your reception or right after dinner. [/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="How the wedding party travel to the reception?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]You and your partner might have the perfect ceremony exit planned, but don't forget you're also responsible for getting your wedding party to the reception. If you're going casual and want them to simply drive over, let everyone know this beforehand so they can carpool or organize transportation ahead of time.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Where should you put your engagement ring?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Wear your engagement ring on your right hand or have someone you trust hold it for you. If you want to wear your engagement ring for the reception, you can put it on after the ceremony. For Jewish weddings, it's fine to wear your engagement ring and then exchange wedding bands if you want to keep with tradition. Also remember: The wedding band is usually worn closest to your heart (first on your finger) on your left hand.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Does the bride need someone to hold the dress?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]You've likely seen this stunt done in romantic comedies, and whether or not you'll have to get this sort of royal treatment depends on the dress. A full-length ball gown will probably require an extra set of hands to hold up the skirt while you do your thing. Trust us—the cost versus the benefit on this is a no-brainer. But if you're sporting a silk sheath and a group bathroom trip makes you cringe, go ahead and fly solo.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Is there a right way to do the first kiss?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]We probably don't need to tell you to keep it PG, but your first kiss as a married couple definitely doesn't have to be just a peck. Do what comes naturally to you both as long as you don't catch your partner by surprise or do anything you'll regret in a few years when you're rewatching your wedding video.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][/vc_accordion][/vc_column][vc_column offset="vc_col-lg-6 vc_col-md-6"][vc_accordion accordion_style="style-one"][vc_accordion_tab title="What's the best way to greet guests?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]We get it—you don't want to stand around after the ceremony in an assembly line. Instead, greet your guests during the reception by stopping by each table during the first course. Just make sure you have time to eat too. Also, make a short speech thanking guests for coming and give a shoutout to vendors and parents.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Can you take your shoes off at any time?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]e've all been to weddings where guests cut loose on the dance floor and ditch the uncomfortable footwear for bear feet or flats. However, the thought of stepping on something sharp (or getting stepped on by a stiletto) and risking an injury early on in the night is a little too much for us to endorse going barefoot. [/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Are there other wedding events I’m invited to?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Everbody is welcome to our day-after brunch on Sunday, October 17! The brunch will be held at the downstairs restaurant of the Eden Roc starting at 10 a.m. A separate invitation will be included in your wedding welcome bag when you arrive at the hotel.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Will transportation provided to the ceremony?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]We have arranged for Uber ride passes for our event! When booking your Uber ride please use the promo code 54Y7 to receive the discount. P.S. The reserved hotels are a short ride away from the ceremony/reception location.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="How many guests can your venue accommodate?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]We can accommodate up to 250 ceremony guests depending on which space is requested. For wedding receptions we can accommodate up to 194 in the Reiman Ballroom, 300 guests in Reiman Ballroom and Mente/Boyd Reception Area, and up to 500 utilizing the entire building for a less formal reception. Contact the events staff for examples of diagrams and room setups.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Are there any cleaning, overtime charges?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]The Alumni Center reserves the right to charge a damage/cleaning fee if necessary after the wedding. There are no overtime charges; however, the guest and client must exit per the agreed upon time. Proof of liability insurance may be required. Security may also be required at the expense of the client.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Must I use vendors of your choosing?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]We require a caterer from our list of approved caterers. We also have a list of vendor partners for vendors other than caterers, but do not require you to select from this list. We ask that you provide us with names and contact information of the vendors you are working with so we may assist with making day of arrangements, especially for vendors whom have never been to our venue.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][/vc_accordion][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row_content_no_spaces" overlay_dotted=""][vc_column css=".vc_custom_1539070052313{padding-top: 0px !important;}"][havnor_callout call_style="three" call_title="Join With Us To Celebrate Our Love..." btn_text="Connect Now" btn_link="#0" open_link="true" btn_text_color="#95c6b7" btn_text_hover_color="#ffffff" btn_bg_color="#ffffff" btn_bg_hover_color="rgba(255,255,255,0.03)" btn_border_color="#ffffff" btn_border_hover_color="#ffffff" title_size="34px"][/havnor_callout][/vc_column][/vc_row]
CONTENT;
    array_unshift($data, $template);
    return $data;
  }

